## `_check_nlink(conn) -> list[FsckIssue]`
<!-- checksum: fsck-8 -->

### Purpose
Verify `nlink(dir) == 2 + count(subdirs)`. Note: this cannot check file nlink correctness without running the full hard-link accounting; for v1 we check directories only.

### Implementation Notes

```python
def _check_nlink(conn):
    rows = conn.execute("""
        SELECT n.inode, n.nlink,
               (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM nodes c
                WHERE c.parent = n.inode AND c.kind = 'dir') AS subdirs
        FROM nodes n
        WHERE n.kind = 'dir'
    """).fetchall()
    return [
        FsckIssue(kind="nlink_mismatch", inode=r[0],
                  detail=f"dir {r[0]} has nlink={r[1]} but {r[2]} subdirs (expected {r[2] + 2})")
        for r in rows
        if r[1] != r[2] + 2
    ]
```

### Test Strategy
- `test_nodes.test_dir_nlink_counts_subdirs` — positive-path check of the invariant this validates.

